The paper deals with cooperative communications with energy harvesting relays, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a distributed power control mechanism using reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method through simulations, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
